## Task: Evolution: Knowledge base grows unboundedly with duplicate lessons

## Problem

\`AuditLogger.UpdateKnowledge()\` in \`internal/evolution/audit.go\` appends every lesson to the knowledge base file unconditionally. There is no deduplication — the same lesson text gets appended every cycle. Over 31 evolution cycles, the knowledge base accumulates redundant entries that:

1. Inflate the context sent to the Reflector (which reads the entire knowledge base)
2. Waste LLM tokens on processing duplicate information
3. Make the knowledge base unreadable for human review

The config has \`MaxPromptBullets: 50\` but this value is never used anywhere in the codebase.

## How to Fix

1. Before appending, check if a lesson with the same ID already exists in the knowledge base
2. Implement the MaxPromptBullets config — when the knowledge base exceeds this limit, summarize/prune old entries
3. Consider using structured storage (JSONL) instead of markdown for the knowledge base to enable reliable deduplication

## How to Test

1. Call \`UpdateKnowledge\` twice with the same lesson ID — assert it appears only once
2. Call \`UpdateKnowledge\` with MaxPromptBullets=5 and 10 lessons — assert pruning occurs
3. Read back the knowledge base and verify it's parseable and non-redundant
